climbs.name: Hump or Die
climbs.fa: Randy Garcia, Brian Keon, Eric Pospesil

content.description:
Climb the short slab to a bolt, move left to a bulge with a beautiful hand crack. Use the hand crack to hump your way over the bulge. Climb the crack as it narrows into a finger crack. Keep moving up once the crack disappears to another bolt. Make some tough slab moves finishing up and right to the tree anchor. 

  There is a 5.7 second pitch that continues up and through the trees to another tree anchor.
content.protection: Standard Rack poissibly extras in #2 or #3 cams and Bolts
content.location: Starts on the small slab just before the trail for Whine and Cheese breaks off steeply up and left. It is the only small slab with one bolt.

content.description: A smaller area containing two quality climbs with a mix of both slab and crack climbing.
